{{page-title "Documentation — Job Posts"}}
<div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl py-6 px-4 space-y-6">

  <Panel::Card>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">Job Posts</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      A Job Post is a stored copy of a job listing. It is the root resource in Career Caddy —
      scores, cover letters, summaries, applications, and scrapes all attach to a Job Post.
      Before you can do anything meaningful with a role, you need to save it here.
    </p>
    {{!-- <img src="" alt="screenshot of the job posts list" /> --}}
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Two Ways to Add a Job Post</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">Manual Entry</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
          Paste the job title, company name, job description, and URL directly into the form.
          Best for listings where scraping is blocked or you're copying from a PDF.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">Scrape from URL</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
          Paste the job listing URL and Career Caddy fetches the page, extracts the content,
          and pre-fills the form. Review the extracted fields before saving. This is the faster
          path for most public job boards.
        </p>
        {{!-- <img src="" alt="screenshot of the scrape form with a URL entered" /> --}}
      </div>
    </div>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">What Flows From a Job Post</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
      Once a Job Post is saved, you can generate or attach:
    </p>
    <ul class="space-y-1 text-gray-600 text-sm list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Score</strong> — AI fit analysis of your profile vs. this role</li>
      <li><strong>Cover Letter</strong> — AI-written in your voice for this specific role</li>
      <li><strong>Summary</strong> — tailored executive summary for your resume or application</li>
      <li><strong>Application</strong> — your record of actually applying, with status tracking</li>
      <li><strong>Scrapes</strong> — the raw page capture(s) this post was derived from</li>
      <li><strong>Questions</strong> — application questions tied to this role</li>
    </ul>
    {{!-- <img src="" alt="screenshot of a job post detail page showing linked resources" /> --}}
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Example Job Post</h2>
    <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded p-4 text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
      <div><span class="font-semibold">Title:</span> Senior Full-Stack Engineer</div>
      <div><span class="font-semibold">Company:</span> Acme Corp</div>
      <div><span class="font-semibold">URL:</span> <span class="text-blue-600">https://jobs.acme.example/sfullstack-123</span></div>
      <div><span class="font-semibold">Posted:</span> March 28, 2026</div>
      <div class="pt-1">
        <span class="font-semibold">Description:</span>
        <p class="mt-1 text-gray-600">
          We are looking for a Senior Full-Stack Engineer to join our platform team. You'll own
          features end-to-end across our Python backend and Ember.js frontend. We care about
          code quality, pragmatic architecture, and shipping software that works. 5+ years
          experience required. Remote-friendly.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    {{!-- <img src="" alt="screenshot of this example job post in the show view" /> --}}
  </Panel::Card>

</div>
